<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,810,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,591,810,835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Female macroptera and microptera</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[611,747,810,834]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 20. S" captionStartId="5.[151,264,924,947]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,193,903]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 20. S. houji: (18) macropterous female, (19) micropterous female, (20) micropterous male (Scale bar = 200 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278574/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Figs 
<number box="[673,747,810,834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="18.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="18.0">18–19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distended body length about 1.0– 
<quantity box="[1171,1264,810,834]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
. Head, thorax, abdominal terga VII–X and antennal segments IV–VIII brown; abdominal terga I–III pale brown, IV–VI paler; antecostal ridges on terga II–VII dark brown (Fig. 
<number box="[737,753,879,903]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="6.0">6</number>
). Fore wings brown with sub-basal pale band; legs bearing microtrichia, all tibae and tarsus brownish yellow, coxa and femora brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,810,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Head 
<number box="[264,347,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5</number>
times as wide as long (Fig. 
<number box="[669,685,949,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="7.0">7</number>
); three pairs of ocellar setae present, ocellar setae III situated outside of ocellar triangle; occipital apodeme very near to posterior margin of eyes (Fig. 
<number box="[1131,1147,983,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="7.0">7</number>
). Antennae 
<number box="[1286,1298,983,1007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="8.0">8</number>
-segmented, segments III and IV each with forked sensoria (
<figureCitation box="[683,813,1018,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Figs 
<number box="[739,813,1018,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennal segments I–VIII length/width: 
<number box="[1289,1326,1018,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number box="[1337,1374,1018,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="1.5">1.5</number>
, 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="3.25" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.2">3.2– 3.3</number>
, 3.0– 
<number box="[252,286,1053,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="3.1">3.1</number>
, 
<number box="[298,334,1053,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.9">2.9</number>
–3.0, 
<number box="[396,482,1053,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.4</number>
, 
<number box="[494,580,1053,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.55" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.6</number>
, and 
<number box="[639,726,1053,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="3.2" valueMax="3.3" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.3</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,810,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Pronotum 
<number box="[315,398,1087,1111]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1.8–1.9</number>
times as wide as long, reticulate with a large blotch and thick setae; metanotum sculptured, with a pair of median setae situated behind anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[849,933,1122,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[904,933,1122,1146]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); tarsi 
<number box="[1015,1028,1122,1146]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented. Fore wing second vein without setae. Abdominal segments with dense rows of microtrichia across terga; terga I–VIII with posteromarginal comb complete medially, median setae placed equidistant on terga I–VIII (Fig. 
<number box="[1105,1122,1191,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="6.0">6</number>
). Abdominal sterna without discal setae; sterna II–VII with setae on posterior margin, on VII situated anterior to margin (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1276,1226,1250]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[1245,1276,1226,1250]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,810,1805]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,398,1261,1286]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Male microptera</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[413,500,1261,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[513,545,1261,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 18 – 20. S" captionStartId="5.[151,264,924,947]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,193,903]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 18 – 20. S. houji: (18) macropterous female, (19) micropterous female, (20) micropterous male (Scale bar = 200 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278574/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">20</figureCitation>
). Distended body length about 
<number box="[896,932,1261,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="0.9">0.9</number>
–1.0 mm. Similar to female but smaller (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1295,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
); with a small circular pore plate on abdominal sterna IV–VII (
<figureCitation box="[888,972,1295,1319]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1931,1954]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,195,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. (10 – 15) S. houji: (10) abdominal sterna III – IV, (11) meso-metasternum, (12) microptera wing, (13) pore plates on sterna IV – VII (male), (14) antenna (female), (15) antenna (male). (16) H. abdominalis: antenna (female). (17) H. longjingensis sp. n.: antenna (Holotype) (Scale bar = 50 microns)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278573/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number box="[941,972,1295,1319]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
